 Filmmaker Bimpe Akintunde is grateful after God spared her life and the life of her daughter. The star shared the story of how she and her daughter escaped a bandit attack along the Lagos-Ibadan express road. In her post, Bimpe said she was on her way to Lagos when she ran into the bandits at Oni-Garri. She said the bandits were shooting directly at the vehicles on the road. READ ALSO: Actress Adebimpe Adedimeji Thanks Toyin Abraham For Support During Wedding Her story comes barely a week after a driver was killed and five persons were abducted at Oni-Garri along the Lagos-Ibadan expressway. Bimpe how ever told her fans and followers to be careful when traveling that route. Read her account of what happened below:   A post shared by Abiodun Adebimpe Akintunde (@iambimpeakintunde) 